-- Emerging-Market Currencies Set to Gain Versus Dollar on Growth, Pimco Says
-- B y   G a r f i e l d   R e y n o l d s
-- 2010-10-13T21:53:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/emerging-market-currencies-set-to-gain-versus-dollar-on-growth-pimco-says.html
Emerging-market currencies are
likely to rise against the U.S. dollar as consumer demand in
those nations is taking over from U.S. household spending as a
major driver of world economic growth, according to Pacific
Investment Management Co.  Investors seeking to benefit from economic growth in
developing markets may want to look at investing in local-
currency government bonds, Curtis Mewbourne, a managing director
at Newport Beach, California-based Pimco, said on the firmâ€™s
website. Dollar-denominated bonds issued by emerging-market
corporations also may be attractive, he wrote.  To contact the reporter on this story:
